证据片段: The tubing selected for the round robin was typical of current pressurized water reactor (PWR) fuel cladding, with a nominal outer diameter of 0.440 in. and a wall thickness of 0.025 in.

证据片段: The average pre-test diameter measurements agreed very well, with a maximum variation of 0.0003 in. between measurements made by different laboratories on adjacent specimens cut from the same tube.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk3
证据片段: The average wall thickness measurements agreed well for Tests 2-A, 2-B, 3, and 4, but the measurements of Test l-A were on the average 0.0017 in. smaller.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk3
证据片段: It was also found that the wall thickness of Tube 5 was about 0.001 in. thicker than Tubes 1 to 4, which all had approximately the same wall thickness.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk3
证据片段: The UHS results show two distinct groupings: Test Procedures 1-A and 4 are at about 140 ksi for Tubes 1 to 4, and Test Procedures 1-B, 2-A, 2-B, and 3 are at about 130 ksi.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk4
证据片段: The highest accuracy which can be hoped for using either method is $\pm 0 . 0 0 5$ in.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk4
证据片段: Although the two distinct groupings of UHS results differed in strength by almost 10 percent, they also showed close similarities. All tests showed Tube 5 as having the lowest strength, and most showed little difference between the other four tubes.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk4
证据片段: As mentioned in the section on Pre-Test Measurements, the wall thickness measurements of the Test 1-A specimens are on the average 0.0017 in. smaller than those measured in Tests 2-A, 2-B, 3, and 4.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk4
证据片段: The wall thickness measurements for Test 1-B specimens were also lower than for the other three tests, but only by an average of 0.0005 in.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk4
证据片段: Probably the explanation for the slightly higher UHS is because of the higher strain rate above yield, as mentioned in the section on Burst Test Apparatus.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk4
证据片段: A comparison of the UHS of Test 2-A (with mandrel), with that of Test ?-B (no mandrel) shows that the mandrel has little influence on the UHS.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk4
证据片段: In every case where two comparable results are available, the mandrel containing specimens had the higher TCE.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk4
证据片段: This observation is consistent with Table 2 which shows that the standard deviation for all five tubes increases with decreasing diametral clearance.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk5
证据片段: One of the participating laboratories imposes a limit of 130 ft·lb stored energy when the system is pressurized to 8000 psi with a thick-walled specimen in place.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk5
证据片段: Increases in the strain rate tend to increase the UHS and decrease the TCE.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_005_chunk6
证据片段: Ultrasonic nondestructive inspection of fuel tubing can be made far more uniform and reliable by placing proper priority on the various test parameters
